<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1161,1800]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1270,1296]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[619,690,1269,1295]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">China</collectingCountry>
. Distribution covers the marine littoral environments. from 
<collectingCountry box="[1361,1432,1269,1295]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,213,1305,1331]" name="Cuba" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[224,316,1305,1331]" name="Gambia" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Gambia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[327,419,1305,1331]" name="Bahrain" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Bahrain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[430,533,1305,1331]" name="Malaysia" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[547,621,1305,1332]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Sabah</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[640,756,1305,1331]" name="Singapore" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Singapore</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[815,925,1305,1331]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy, D. H." box="[939,1104,1305,1331]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="49 - 63" refId="ref6645" refString="Murphy, D. H. (1971) Revision of the tropical marine littoral genus Pseudanurida Schott (Collembola: Pseudachorutinae). Pacific Insects, 12 (1), 49 - 63." type="journal article" year="1971">Murphy, 1971</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1161,1800]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
The species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[565,633,1341,1367]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and dedicated to Professor Paulo Sawaya (so the correct name is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuster" authorityYear="1965" class="Entognatha" family="Neanuridae" genus="Pseudanurida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sawayai">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Pseudanurida sawayai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuster" authorityYear="1965" box="[460,602,1378,1403]" class="Entognatha" family="Neanuridae" genus="Pseudanurida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sawayana">
<emphasis box="[460,602,1378,1403]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">P. sawayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as originally described and cited in many articles). In the same year of Schuster’s description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy, D. H." box="[414,586,1413,1440]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="388 - 411" refId="ref6597" refString="Murphy, D. H. (1965) Collembola Poduromorpha from the Gambia (West Africa). Journal of Zoology, 146, 388 - 411. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1965. tb 05216. x" type="journal article" year="1965">Murphy (1965)</bibRefCitation>
characterized and illustrated a series of specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1227,1319,1413,1439]" name="Gambia" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Gambia</collectingCountry>
, including the complete dorsal chaetotaxy, which were identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Baker, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[784,1323,1449,1476]" class="Entognatha" family="Neanuridae" genus="Pseudanurida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bogoyawlenskyi">
<emphasis box="[784,941,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Pseudanurida</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[982,1161,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">bogoyawlenskyi</emphasis>
(Baker, 1905)
</taxonomicName>
; however, later 
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy, D. H." box="[208,379,1485,1511]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="49 - 63" refId="ref6645" refString="Murphy, D. H. (1971) Revision of the tropical marine littoral genus Pseudanurida Schott (Collembola: Pseudachorutinae). Pacific Insects, 12 (1), 49 - 63." type="journal article" year="1971">Murphy (1971)</bibRefCitation>
recognized that those specimens were actually of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schuster" authorityYear="1965" box="[943,1062,1486,1511]" class="Entognatha" family="Neanuridae" genus="Pseudanurida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sawayai">
<emphasis box="[943,1062,1486,1511]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">P. sawayai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1161,1800]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
The species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[571,639,1521,1547]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Recife: Barra das Jangadas) in a creek connecting 
<collectingRegion box="[1233,1273,1521,1547]" country="Gambia" name="Upper River" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Rio</collectingRegion>
Pirapama and 
<collectingRegion box="[151,191,1557,1583]" country="Gambia" name="Upper River" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Rio</collectingRegion>
Jaboatão, a few km South of Piedade Marine Biol. Station, in mangroves; nevertheless after 
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy, D. H." box="[1262,1436,1557,1583]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="49 - 63" refId="ref6645" refString="Murphy, D. H. (1971) Revision of the tropical marine littoral genus Pseudanurida Schott (Collembola: Pseudachorutinae). Pacific Insects, 12 (1), 49 - 63." type="journal article" year="1971">Murphy (1971)</bibRefCitation>
it also has been found in 
<collectingCountry box="[437,526,1593,1619]" name="Gambia" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Gambia</collectingCountry>
(West Africa) in mangroves and rocky shore; 
<collectingRegion box="[1051,1119,1593,1619]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Sabah</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1134,1297,1593,1620]" name="Malaysia" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">North Borneo</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[1316,1400,1593,1619]" country="Malaysia" name="Labuan" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Labuan</collectingRegion>
on weed-covered rocks, small inlet inside 
<collectingRegion box="[593,677,1629,1655]" country="Malaysia" name="Labuan" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Labuan</collectingRegion>
town at low tide; 
<collectingCountry box="[886,1002,1629,1655]" name="Singapore" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Singapore</collectingCountry>
, Pasir Ris, sparse mangroves by small stream; 
<collectingCountry box="[241,333,1665,1691]" name="Bahrain" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Bahrain</collectingCountry>
, Persian Gulf, edge of inland, fresh-water stream (maybe of artesian origin); 
<collectingCountry box="[1201,1285,1665,1691]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
, Mendel lake (a brackish lagoon on the West coast) and in Mannar, Giant’s tank (a large, inland, artificial fresh-water lake). It was found by 
<bibRefCitation author="Christiansen, K. A. &amp; Bellinger, P." box="[307,666,1737,1763]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" pagination="215 - 245" refId="ref6164" refString="Christiansen, K. A. &amp; Bellinger, P. (1988) Marine littoral Collembola of North and Central America. Bulletin of Marine Science, 42, 215 - 245." type="journal article" year="1988">Christiansen &amp; Bellinger (1988)</bibRefCitation>
in mangroves of 
<collectingCountry box="[859,994,1737,1764]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, and also under and on rocks in 
<collectingRegion box="[1348,1432,1737,1763]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Florida</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,211,1773,1799]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">USA</collectingCountry>
. Now is has been found in sandy beach, so it seems that this species can live in different habitats.
</paragraph>
